  "content_id": "513da9e6-59a1-4b95-a0aa-0b751020686b",
  "description": "Get a veterans badge for Bevin Boys miners during World War 2 - eligibility, widows, application",
  "details": {
    "body": "\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>You can get a Bevin Boys veterans badge if you worked in the coal mines under the Bevin Boys scheme - widows of Bevin Boys may also be eligible.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2 id=\"eligibility\">Eligibility</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll get a badge if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you worked in the mines under the Bevin Boys scheme between 1943 and 1948</li>\n  <li>you’re the widow of a Bevin Boy who died on or after 20 June 2007</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>All Bevin Boys are eligible - it does not matter if you volunteered or were a ‘ballotee’ (conscript).</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2 id=\"how-to-apply\">How to apply</h2>\n\n<p>There is no fee for applying for a veterans badge.</p>\n\n<p>Fill in a <a href=\"/government/publications/bevin-boys-veterans-badge\">Bevin Boys veterans badge application</a> and send it by email or post to the Coal Liabilities Unit.</p>\n\n<p>Contact the Coal Liabilities Unit if you need help completing the form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p>Coal Liabilities Unit<br>\n<a href=\"mailto:Christine.Mower@beis.gov.uk\">Christine.Mower@beis.gov.uk</a><br>\n07471 358264<br>\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 4pm<br>\n<a href=\"/call-charges\">Find out about call charges</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nCoal Liabilities Unit  \n<br>Department for Energy Security and Net Zero\n<br>Bay 359, Level 3, Orchard 2 \n<br>1 Victoria Street \n<br>London \n<br>SW1H 0ET\n<br>\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2 id=\"after-youve-applied\">After you’ve applied</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll get your badge around 2 to 3 weeks after sending in the application form.</p>\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
